"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714259","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-03-30","<p>The Government will shortly bring forward a Green Paper to examine markets that are not working efficiently or fairly for consumers.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714259/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-30T15:34:38.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714259/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714259/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-03-27","Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to page 55 of the report UK Poverty Causes and Solutions, published by the Joseph Rowntree Foundation, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of implementing the recommendation in that report on the remit of regulations; and if he will make it his policy to implement that recommendation.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","69358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714260","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-04","<p>The Department for International Trade will be releasing its first full year travel and subsistence spend in its Annual Reports and Accounts.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714260/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-04T12:38:02.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714260/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714260/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-03-27","Department for International Trade: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how much his Department has spent on (a) hotels, (b) hospitality, (c) food and drink and (d) transport in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","69224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714261","Department for International Trade","false","2017-03-30","<p>Since April 2016, the Government has spent £1.97m on television advertising as part of the Exporting is GREAT campaign to inspire more businesses to take their next step towards exporting by visiting the website great.gov.uk.</p><p>Television advertising gives us the ability to communicate with a large audience across the UK, generate awareness and encourage action. We target specific audiences and TV is a cost effective medium that compliments other communications activity across radio, print, online and email. This ensures our message reaches the intended audiences.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714261/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-30T15:34:32.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714261/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714261/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-03-27","Trade Promotion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how much the Government has spent on television advertisements urging businesses to export in the last 12 months; and what the business case was for that expenditure.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","69259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714262","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-03-30","<p>The Government has been clear that we will not provide a running commentary on negotiations and the department has no plans to change policy regarding publication of correspondence. DExEU is regularly engaging with leaders of local government and cities. <br><br></p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714262/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-30T15:57:29.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714262/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714262/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-03-27","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what correspondence he has had with leaders of Core Cities on the negotiations for the UK to leave the EU.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","69187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714263","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-03-30","<p>Ministers and officials across Government are engaging UK and EU business from every sector of the economy - this is a central element of our plan to get the right deal for Britain. We are listening and talking to a broad range of organisations, companies and institutions.<br><br>Details of Ministerial meetings will be published in the Department’s Quarterly Transparency Returns, which will be made publicly available on GOV.UK.<br><br></p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714263/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-30T13:33:40.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714263/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714263/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-03-27","Glass: Manufacturing Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what discussions his Department has had with representatives from the glass industry on the implications of the UK leaving the EU; and what plans he has to prioritise that industry in his negotiations on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","69262"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714264","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-03-30","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union, working with officials across Government, continues to undertake a wide range of data analysis covering the entirety of the UK economy. We are looking at over 50 sectors as well as cross-cutting regulatory issues. This will inform the UK's position for the upcoming negotiations with our EU partners. The Government's plan for leaving the EU has been discussed at length, and Parliament will have a say on the final deal we achieve with the European Union by putting that deal to a vote in both Houses before it comes into force. But as Parliament has also agreed, we will not publish anything that would undermine our ability to negotiate the best deal for Britain.<br><br></p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714264/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-30T13:31:30Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714264/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714264/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-03-27","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to his oral contribution of 2 February 2017, Official Report, column 1218, if he will list those 58 economic sectors.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","69306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714265","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-04","<p>Information on ministerial and senior officials gifts, hospitality and travel will be released as part of regular transparency publications on GOV.UK.<br><br><br><br></p><p> </p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714265/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-04T16:36:05.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714265/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714265/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-03-27","Department for Exiting the European Union: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how much his Department has spent on (a) hotels, (b) hospitality, (c) food and drink and (d) transport in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","69219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714266","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-03-30","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on 22 March 2017 to the Question 67738. <br><br>The Department is recruiting the brightest and the best from across the civil service, the wider public sector and the private sector. We will not be providing a running commentary as recruitment is ongoing and numbers are regularly changing.<strong><br></strong></p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714266/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-30T15:49:19.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714266/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714266/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-03-27","Department for Exiting the European Union: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 22 March 2017 to Question 67738, on Department for Exiting the European Union: secondment, how many secondees to his Department were from (a) PwC, (b) Deloitte, (c) Accenture, (d) McKinsey & Co, (f) Ernst and Young and (g) Bain & Company.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","69178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714279","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-07","<p>The total budget for High Speed 2 is £55.7bn. HS2 Ltd is currently procuring contractors to deliver the first Phase of HS2. The Department for Transport does not release details of the estimated cost of constructing individual components of the scheme as this information is commercially sensitive.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714279/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-07T12:34:27.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714279/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714279/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-27","High Speed 2 Railway Line","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon on 21 March (HL6081), what is their estimate of the cost of constructing the Handsacre connection to the West Coast Main Line compared with a straight connection to HS2 Phase 2A towards Crewe.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL6300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714280","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-03","<p>HS2 Ltd is funded by the Government, whereas Bazalgette Tunnel Ltd and Thames Water Utilities Ltd are not, and as such, different arrangements apply in respect of the information which the Government can request from them and the extent to which it can be disclosed.</p><p> </p><p>In the particular case of information about CH2M Hill staff referred to in the noble Lord’s previous question (HL5813), this is not required by the Secretary of State to carry out her functions, and Defra therefore does not hold it.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714280/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-03T16:13:06.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714280/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714280/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-27","CH2M Hill","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answers by Lord Gardiner of Kimble on 16 March (HL5813 and HL5815), since HS2 Ltd, Thames Water Utilities Ltd and Bazalgette Tunnel Ltd are all private limited companies, why the information requested is available for HS2 but not the other companies.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL6301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714281","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-07","<p>The current West Coast Main Line (WCML) has been optimised for tilting trains which operate up to a maximum speed of 125 mph, whilst non-tilting trains are limited to operating at up to 110 mph.</p><p> </p><p>However, north of the future Golborne Junction, track geometry on some sections of line may allow non-tilting passenger trains to operate up to 125 mph within the existing operational rules and without track changes. Further, minor infrastructure alternations could be made on the transitions between straight and curved sections of track to optimise the speed profile for non-tilting trains further, which would make no change to the speed profile of existing tilting trains. The journey time differential between a tilting train and non-tilting train would therefore be reduced.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714281/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-07T12:34:03.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714281/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714281/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-27","West Coast Railway Line","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon on 23 March (HL5994), what are the minor line speed improvements on the West Coast Main Line, mainly North of Preston, that will enable non-tilt trains to go faster, but will not enable tilting trains to go faster.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL6302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714282","Department for Education","false","2017-03-30","<p>The Student Loans Company publishes an annual statistical first release on student loans in England that provides statistics on loan outlays, repayment of loans and borrower activity. The latest release is attached.</p><p>In addition to this, in February 2016 the Department published a Joint Repayment Strategy which includes an assessment of actions to trace borrowers and to recover loans where avoidance or evasion is identified. This publication isalso attached.</p>",,"Viscount Younger of Leckie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714282/answer","Debt_and_repayment_statistics_England_2016.xlsx ; Student-loan-repayment-for-sustainable-higher-education-strategy-February-2016.pdf","Debt_and_repayment_statistics_England_2016.xlsx ; Student-loan-repayment-for-sustainable-higher-education-strategy-February-2016.pdf","Debt_and_repayment_statistics_England_2016 ; Student-loan-repayment-sustainable-higher-educatio","Debt_and_repayment_statistics_England_2016 ; Student-loan-repayment-sustainable-higher-educatio",,"2017-03-30T17:01:30.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714282/answer","Biography information for Viscount Younger of Leckie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714282/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-03-27","Overseas Students: Loans","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the effectiveness of methods of recovery of student loans from overseas students.","false","Biography information for Baroness Deech",,"Baroness Deech","HL6303"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714283","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-05","<p>The Marriage Allowance was introduced in 2015-16 to recognise the importance of marriage in the tax system. Around 1.8m people have claimed the allowance to date.</p><p> </p><p>Our current best estimate assessment of the initial cost of this allowance is £140m in 2015-16, but this does not include the impact of any expected future claims, which can be backdated to this year. We forecast the total cost of this allowance to rise to £385m in 2015-16 once these claims are taken into account.</p><p> </p><p>An estimate of the initial cost of this allowance for 2016-17 will not be available until the end of the tax year. We forecast an eventual cost to the exchequer of £425m, once all backdated claims are taken into account.</p><p> </p><p>Marriage Allowance claims can be made up to 4 years after the tax year has finished. The expected future projections of the Marriage Allowance final cost for 2019-20 is not available because this depends on our forecast of backdated applications, and the forecast period does not currently extend out to 2023-24.</p><p> </p><p>HM Treasury does not hold information relating to the income deciles of claimants or successful applicants of the Marriage Allowance. Previous analysis of the total eligible population has shown the majority of the benefits of this policy go to the bottom half of the income distribution. Only basic rate taxpayers and non-taxpayers will benefit.</p><p> </p><p>HM Treasury does not hold information about how many individuals claiming Universal Credit are eligible for the Marriage Allowance.</p><p> </p><p>The number of claimants of Married Couple's Allowance by the income groups requested is set out for the latest outturn year available (2014-15):</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Thousand</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p>Percentile Groups (ranged on total income before tax)</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bottom 20%</p></td><td><p>20%-50%</p></td><td><p>Top 50%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>31</p></td><td><p>304</p></td><td><p>385</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The cost of the Married Couples Allowance is forecast to be £220m in 2016-17. It is expected that the cost of this relief will decline, as it is restricted to couples where at least one of them is born before 6 April 1935.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714283/answer",,,,,"HL6282 ; HL6283 ; HL6284 ; HL6285 ; HL6286 ; HL6305 ; HL6306","2017-04-05T10:58:43.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714283/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714283/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-27","Married People: Tax Allowances","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much was budgeted for Married Couples Allowance in 2016–17; and what are their future expenditure projections.","false","Biography information for Lord Farmer",,"Lord Farmer","HL6304"
