"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713425","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-03-28","<p>The department is in consultation with all stakeholders its to understand how leaving the EU will impact them, including the UK telecoms industry. We want our new partnership with the EU to minimise the regulatory and market access barriers for both goods and services.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713425/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T14:41:23.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713425/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713425/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-23","Telecommunications: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what contingency plans the Government has made to ensure that broadband and telecom companies are not left operating under the current regulatory framework in the event that the new European Electronic Communications Code is not transposed into UK law before the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Calum Kerr","Berwickshire, Roxburgh and Selkirk","Calum Kerr","69005"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713426","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-03-28","<p>The Government is currently assessing the EU Electronic Communications Code. No such proposal for divergence has been made.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713426/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T14:39:44.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713426/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713426/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-23","Telecommunications: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment the Government has made of the cost to UK telecoms providers of any divergence between EU and UK electronic communications regulatory regimes after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Calum Kerr","Berwickshire, Roxburgh and Selkirk","Calum Kerr","69006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713427","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-03-28","<p>The Government is currently assessing the full impact the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) will have on areas of data processing. The UK made several interventions throughout the negotiations on the GDPR, with support from industry, which have secured real benefits and avoided excessive burdens on business.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713427/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T11:10:11.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713427/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713427/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-23","Telecommunications: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment the Government has made of the cost to UK telecoms providers of any divergence between EU and UK data protection laws after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Calum Kerr","Berwickshire, Roxburgh and Selkirk","Calum Kerr","69007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713428","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-03-28","<p>My Department has regular discussions with other Government Departments on a range of issues impacting on the regulation of the telecoms sector and regularly receives proposals which contribute to policy development, which are considered on their merits as part of this process.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713428/answer",,,,,"68946","2017-03-28T11:11:00.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713428/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713428/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-23","Telecommunications: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment the Government has made of the potential effect on the Dark Fibre Access remedy proposal for BT by Ofcom of the policy of levying business rates on BT customers.","false","Biography information for Calum Kerr","Berwickshire, Roxburgh and Selkirk","Calum Kerr","69008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713429","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-26","<p>The Department spent a) £4,287,620.34 on the Go Superfast advertising campaign in 2014 and b) £3,438,000 in 2015. The campaign increased public awareness of, and interest in, superfast broadband in order to drive take up across the UK.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713429/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-26T09:11:22.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713429/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713429/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-23","Broadband: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much her Department spent on the Go Superfast advertising campaign in (a) 2014 and (b) 2015.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","69029"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713430","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-03-30","<p>The Government is focused on securing the best deal for Britain. As we set out in the UK Digital Strategy, we continue to engage with businesses and key stakeholders to support the UK's digital economy. We will listen to their concerns, aim to limit uncertainty in the transition and ensure our new relationship with the EU works for business and consumers.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713430/answer",,,,,"69030 ; 69031","2017-03-30T12:25:57.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713430/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713430/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-23","Electronic Commerce: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of the effect on UK firms engaged in the digital economy of the UK being outwith an EU-wide VAT regime for that economy.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","69009"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713431","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-03-30","<p>The Government is focused on securing the best deal for Britain. As we set out in the UK Digital Strategy, we continue to engage with businesses and key stakeholders to support the UK's digital economy. We will listen to their concerns, aim to limit uncertainty in the transition and ensure our new relationship with the EU works for business and consumers.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713431/answer",,,,,"69009 ; 69031","2017-03-30T12:25:57.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713431/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713431/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-23","Electronic Commerce: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of the effect on UK firms engaged in the digital economy of proposed changes to the VAT regime for the EU Digital Single Market.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","69030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713432","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-03-30","<p>The Government is focused on securing the best deal for Britain. As we set out in the UK Digital Strategy, we continue to engage with businesses and key stakeholders to support the UK's digital economy. We will listen to their concerns, aim to limit uncertainty in the transition and ensure our new relationship with the EU works for business and consumers.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713432/answer",,,,,"69009 ; 69030","2017-03-30T12:25:57.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713432/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713432/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-23","Electronic Commerce","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of the effect on UK firms engaged in the digital economy of the UK leaving the European Single Market.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","69031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713433","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-03-31","<p>The department is in consultation with all stakeholders its to understand how leaving the EU will impact them, including the UK telecoms industry. We want our new partnership with the EU to allow for tariff free trade in goods and to minimise the regulatory and market access barriers for both goods and services.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713433/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-31T10:45:10.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713433/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713433/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-23","Telecommunications: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of the effect on UK firms engaged in the digital economy if the UK were to be outwith the EU Electronic Communications Framework.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","69032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713434","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-26","<p>It is not possible to get a regional split for all media spend as the campaign was bought on a national basis.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713434/answer",,,,,,"2017-04-26T09:12:39.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713434/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713434/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-23","Broadband: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much the Government spent on advertising for its Go Superfast campaign by (a) the smallest available geographic area, (b) city and (c) region.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","69014"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713435","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-29","<p>The Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 indicated our intention to procure the P-8A Poseidon maritime patrol aircraft and approval for the acquisition, through a Foreign Military Sale arrangement with the United States Government, occured in July 2016.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713435/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-29T15:42:08.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713435/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713435/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-23","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when the decision was taken to purchase the P-8A Poseidon aircraft with the same configuration as those operated by the US Navy.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","69013"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713436","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-29","<p>There are currently nine regimental mascots within Her Majesty's Armed Forces, all of them in the Army. Like all animals employed within Defence, each regimental mascot is provided with food, bedding, veterinary services and reasonable accommodation. Professional veterinary advice is provided in relation to each animal's health and welfare needs and each is subject to annual inspection by a veterinary officer. All mascots are cared for by the regiments they serve. Most serve until they are deceased, however for those that do retire, a suitable home is found.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713436/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-29T15:51:56.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713436/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713436/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-23","Ministry of Defence: Animal Welfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to ensure the welfare of regimental animals in the armed forces; and if he will make it his policy to ensure that regimental animals are properly looked after once they have left active service.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","68969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713437","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-31","<p>The new contract with Neopost will mean Britain's Armed Forces will continue to receive hard copy, secure mail, including photos from their loved ones for free, with no break in service as the new imail INtouch system replaces the e-bluey on 1 April 2017. This was announced on 27 March 2017.</p><p>The e-bluey was a hybrid mail service which enabled service personnel stationed or deployed overseas to receive letters and photographs in hard copy format, but which were sent via email. e-bluey usage has declined by 98% since 2007.</p><p>The iMail Intouch system is more modern and better value for money, allowing users to send up to eight pages including high definition photographs and official documents. Savings will be reinvested in welfare provision for the benefit of Service personnel, including the improvement of internet connections in theatre, ensuring that we continue to maintain world-class communications services for our deployed personnel.</p><p>Letter and parcel services for personnel and their families will continue as before, with hand-written letters sent free of charge via a Forces Free Air Letter.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713437/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-31T13:50:26.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713437/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713437/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-23","Armed Forces: Communication","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department has any plans for discontinuance of access by armed forces personnel to the e-bluey service.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","68970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713438","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-29","<p>Information about the non-competitive contracts that the Ministry of Defence has awarded is published on gov.uk at the following link: https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mod-trade-industry-and-contracts-2016.</p><p>The annex to table 3A of the excel tables provides an analysis of how much has been paid to individual companies through competitive and non-competitive contracts in 2015-16. The information for 2016-17 will be published later this year, in line with the planned Official Statistics release calendar. Updates will be published annually thereafter.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713438/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-29T15:41:33.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713438/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713438/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-23","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much has been paid by his Department to which companies through single source contracts.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","69033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713439","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-29","<p>The Type 45 Power Improvement Project is being procured through competition. Subject to securing the necessary formal approval, our aim is to have completed the competitive process and be in a position to award the contract in early 2018.</p><p>The programme cost and the timetable for completing the work will be determined at the main investment decision point.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713439/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-29T15:43:12.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713439/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713439/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-23","Type 45 Destroyers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of the Type 45 power improvement programme; and if he will publish a new timetable for that programme.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","69015"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713440","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-30","<p>The Intelligence and Security Committee does not comment on the details of its work programme. Where appropriate, it publishes information on visits it has undertaken in its annual reports.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713440/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-30T15:16:58.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713440/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713440/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-23","USA: Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on what dates any member of the Intelligence and Security Committee visited a US military base in the UK in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","68863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713441","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-31","<p>The current approved budget for the dredging works and related activities is around £60 million, inclusive of VAT.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713441/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-31T13:15:32.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713441/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713441/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-23","Aircraft Carriers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost to the public purse is of dredging Portsmouth Harbour to allow the Queen Elizabeth carriers to enter Her Majesty's Naval Base Portsmouth.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","68817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713442","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","true","2017-03-28","<p>​The INF Treaty is a <del class="ministerial">bilateral</del> Treaty between the US <del class="ministerial">and</del> Russia<del class="ministerial">,</del> <ins class="ministerial">and other successor States of the Soviet Union, </ins>so it would be for those <del class="ministerial">States</del> <ins class="ministerial">countries<ins class="ministerial"> </ins></ins>in the first instance to determine any breaches. Iskander is usually regarded as a short-range rather than an intermediate-range missile. The INF Treaty plays a vital role in maintaining Euro-Atlantic security, and we urge Russia to ensure full and verifiable compliance.</p><p>We and our NATO Allies monitor closely the deployment of Russian military assets to Kaliningrad. NATO has made clear that Russia should avoid all actions that could destabilise security in its neighbourhood.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713442/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T16:47:19.737Z","2017-04-04T09:46:02.027Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713442/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713442/answer","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713442/answer/previousversion/42692","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Russia: Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the deployment by Russia of Iskander missiles to Kaliningrad constitutes a breach of the Intermediate-Range Nuclear Forces Treaty; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","68829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713443","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-29","<p>The UK contributed one of our Type 45 Destroyers, HMS DARING, and her crew to the Pakistani Navy-hosted exercise AMAN 17 in February 2017.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713443/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-29T15:40:48.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713443/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713443/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-23","Pakistan: Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what UK military (a) assets and (b) personnel took part in exercise AMAN 17 off the coast of Karachi, Pakistan in February 2017.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","68826"
