ation in Venezuela.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","East Devon","Sir Hugo Swire","68907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713477","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-31","<p>We share the concerns of the international community about the deteriorating political and economic situation in Venezuela. Economic mismanagement is producing inflation and shortages of basic goods, with a significant impact upon ordinary Venezuelans. Venezuela became an FCO Human Rights Priority Country in 2016. President Maduro has requested United Nations assistance to boost medical supplies.</p><p>The Organisation of American States (OAS) has called for the OAS Democratic Charter to be invoked unless the Venezuelan Government calls elections and releases political prisoners. The UNASUR- supported dialogue between the Government and opposition has stalled.</p><p>I met the previous Venezuelan Minister for Europe, Samuel Moncada at the EU-CELAC Foreign Minister's meeting on 26 October and discussed humanitarian issues and the economic situation. At that meeting I also raised the deteriorating situation in Venezuela with several of my Latin American and European counterparts. On 20 March I met a delegation of Venezuelan MPs from the National Assembly to discuss the situation and to highlight our support for an independent and empowered Parliament. The EU Foreign Affairs Committee last discussed Venezuela on 18 July, which was attended by the Foreign Secretary.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713477/answer",,,,,"68904 ; 68905 ; 68906 ; 68907","2017-03-31T13:38:43.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713477/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713477/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Venezuela: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his counterparts in Latin America on the political and economic situation in Venezuela.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","East Devon","Sir Hugo Swire","68908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713478","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-31","<p>​We take our arms export responsibilities very seriously. The key test for our arms exports to members of the Saudi-led coalition is whether there is a clear risk that the items concerned might be used in the commission of a serious violation of international humanitarian law. The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend, the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Mr Johnson), is in regular communication with the Secretary of State for International Trade, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for North Somerset (Dr Fox), on these issues.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713478/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-31T10:44:45.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713478/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713478/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for International Trade on UK arms sales to the Saudi-led coalition forces operating in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","68902"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713479","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-30","<p>During his recent visit to the region My Rt Hon. Friend the Foreign Secretary (Mr Johnson), discussed the drought at his meetings with President Farmajo, Kenyan Cabinet Secretary for Foreign Affairs, Amina Mohamed, and Prime Minister Hailemariam and emphasised the UK's steadfast support for the international humanitarian effort. Somalia, Kenya, and Ethiopia are facing a severe drought, and parts of South Sudan are already in famine. On 22 and 23 March the Foreign Secretary chaired UN Security Council meetings during which President Farmajo called for greater support for Somalia, and the Council collectively expressed deep alarm at the famine and continued violence in South Sudan.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713479/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-30T13:37:47.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713479/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713479/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","East Africa: Famine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his counterparts in (a) Somalia, (b) Kenya, (c) Ethiopia and (b) South Sudan on famine in that region.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","68903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713480","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>​Officials at the British High Commission in Kigali are in touch with local authorities and providing consular assistance to Violette Uwamahoro, including visiting her in detention. Consular officials are also in contact with her family.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713480/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T13:44:51.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713480/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713480/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Violette Uwamahoro","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what support his Department is providing to Violette Uwamahoro and her family following her arrest and detention in Rwanda.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","68918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713481","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>None. Decisions on visas for entry to the United States are a matter for the Government of the United States.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713481/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T16:42:18.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713481/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713481/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Africa: Sustainable Development","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to his US counterparts on the barring of African delegates from the US summit on Sustainable Development in Africa in March 2017.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","68945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713482","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-30","<p>The UK is a strong supporter of the Human Rights Council. We were proud to be re-elected as members last year. It is in all our interests to strengthen the rules-based international system. But the Council’s current approach of a hugely disproportionate focus on Israel does not support human rights in the Occupied Palestinian Territories, nor further the goal of a two-state solution. US engagement in the Human Rights Council is a matter for the US Government and we would not issue a statement regarding it.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713482/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-30T13:43:21.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713482/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713482/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Occupied Territories: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make an assessment of the potential effect of US withdrawal from the UN Human Rights Council on human rights violations in the Occupied Palestinian Territories; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Mr Gavin Shuker","68958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713483","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-30","<p>The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Mr Johnson), has not met with any of Syria's Kurdish political parties, though he and I have both met with leaders of the High Negotiations Committee and National Coalition of the Syrian Opposition, both of which include the Kurdish National Council as a constituent member.</p><p>Officials in London and across our Syria Overseas Network meet regularly with representatives from the Kurdish National Council. UK officials have also met, less frequently, with representatives from the Kurdish Democratic Union Party (PYD).</p><p>Through our Embassy in Turkey we also regularly engage with Kurdish political parties, including the Peoples' Democratic Party, the HDP (Halk Demokratik Partisi). It is important that we maintain a dialogue with all the main political parties.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713483/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-30T13:41:07.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713483/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713483/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Kurds: Political Parties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has had recent discussions with Kurdish political parties in Syria and Turkey.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","68947"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713484","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-31","<p>​We monitor human rights in Turkey and regularly engage with Turkey on human rights at Ministerial level as well as via our Embassy network in Turkey. I raised human rights with Turkish counterparts most recently on 25 March during my latest visit to Turkey. We will continue to urge Turkey to uphold the rights of all its citizens, regardless of ethnicity and faith.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713484/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-31T13:20:34.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713484/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713484/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Turkey: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his Turkish counterpart on human rights and alleged religious persecution in that country.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","68948"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713485","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>​The Prime Minister met President Poroshenko at Davos in January. We are preparing for him to visit the UK and meet the Prime Minister, at her invitation, in the near future.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713485/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T15:00:14.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713485/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713485/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Petro Poroshenko","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether President Poroshenko has been invited to visit the UK to meet the Prime Minister.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","68964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713486","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>​We have frequent discussions with the Government of Israel about the need to ease restrictions on Gaza. Easing restrictions would alleviate the suffering of ordinary Palestinians, advance construction, and allow the Gazan economy to grow. We are also urging Egypt to show maximum flexibility in opening the Rafah crossing. A durable agreement is necessary to safeguard Egypt and Israel’s security; it must include Hamas and other terrorist groups permanently ending rocket fire.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713486/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T13:47:06.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713486/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713486/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Gaza: Reconstruction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make an assessment of the steps necessary to ensure the economic redevelopment of the Gaza Strip; and what steps can be taken to facilitate such redevelopment without affecting the security of Egypt and Israel.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","68966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713487","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>We are aware of this case and are following it closely. We have raised before to the Emiratis the importance of due process in criminal proceedings, upholding international standards of justice and ensuring the human rights of all Emirati citizens are fully respected, including the rights of freedom of expression and association.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713487/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T13:48:53.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713487/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713487/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Ahmed Mansoor","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government has made to the Government of United Arab Emirates on the detention of Emirati human rights defender Ahmed Mansoor in that country.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","69021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713488","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>​Sanctions are having an impact on Russia, exacerbating negative trends in its economy caused by low oil prices and structural weakness. The Russian economy contracted by approximately 3.7% in 2015 and by 0.5% in 2016. Financial sanctions are particularly effective, making it expensive and difficult for sanctioned Russian entities to access finance to rollover existing debt and fund new investment projects.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713488/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T15:02:49.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713488/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713488/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Russia: Sanctions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of international economic sanctions against Russia related to that country's occupation of parts of Ukraine.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","68996"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713489","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>I hold regular meetings with the Ukrainian Ambassador, Her Excellency Ambassador, Natalia Galibarenko. The most recent was in January, during which we had a wide ranging discussion both bilateral and international issues.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713489/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T15:04:30.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713489/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713489/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Ukraine: Diplomatic Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he last met the Ukrainian Ambassador to the UK.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","68997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713490","Cabinet Office","false","2017-03-31","<p>The first duty of Government is to safeguard the nation, and we treat the security of our democratic processes extremely seriously.</p><p>Our system of paper balloting and hand counting means UK voting mechanisms do not lend themselves to direct electronic manipulation. However, the Government has in place a number of measures to protect the integrity of the electoral process from malign activity, including from cyber attack.</p><p>The National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC) offers UK organisations, including political parties, access to the best cyber security advice and support to help them meet their responsibility to protect their information and prevent cyber attacks from all possible threats.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713490/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-31T14:22:51.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713490/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713490/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-23","Electronic Warfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment the Government has made of the current level of threat to democracy in the UK from cyber attacks, propaganda and subversion by hostile states; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","69045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713491","Department of Health","false","2017-03-28","<p>PHILIP DUNNE</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The NHS Litigation Authority (NHSLA) collects data by specialty. Although maternity is not listed as a specialty, Obstetrics specialty data is collected.</p><p> </p><p>The following table shows the number of successful negligence claims against the National Health Service and the cost of such claims.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Closure Year</p></td><td><p>Number. of Claims</p></td><td><p>Total Estimate</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(Settlement Year for Periodical Payment Orders)</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>(total paid and an estimate of<br> total damages for claims settling as Periodical Payment Orders)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>709</p></td><td><p>£713,275,314</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>651</p></td><td><p>£717,281,270</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>690</p></td><td><p>£629,835,417</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>610</p></td><td><p>£692,266,887</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>Source:</em> NHSLA</p><p><em>Date:</em> March 2017</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713491/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T14:40:30.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713491/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713491/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-23","Maternity Services: Negligence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many successful negligence claims against NHS England maternity services there have been in each year since 2012; and what estimate he has made of the cost of such claims to NHS England in each such year.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","69049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713492","Department of Health","false","2017-03-28","<p>The provision of cough assist machines is a matter for local clinical commissioning groups (CCGs). CCGs have the independence and autonomy to make commissioning decisions for local populations, taking into account the available evidence and individual circumstances as appropriate.</p><p>The evidence base to support the routine use of cough assist machines in muscle-wasting conditions over other cough assist methods is not well established. NHS England worked with Muscular Dystrophy UK through its Bridging the Gap project to address areas of concern raised by patients and their representatives, one of which was the provision of cough assist machines. Through this work, a number of CCGs developed commissioning policies which set out the circumstances in which to consider these devices. In addition, in February 2016 the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence published new guidance on the assessment and management of motor neurone disease, recommending that cough assist machines should be considered if assisted breath stacking is not effective, and/or during a respiratory tract infection.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713492/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T09:21:32.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713492/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713492/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-23","Muscular Dystrophy: Medical Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to encourage clinical commissioning groups to follow best practice commissioning policy on access to cough assist machines for people with muscle-wasting conditions.","false","Biography information for Dr Philippa Whitford","Central Ayrshire","Dr Philippa Whitford","69050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713493","Department of Health","false","2017-03-30","<p>The Department has not made a recent assessment of the diagnosis of encephalitis or the level of National Health Service support available to people who have been diagnosed with encephalitis.</p><p> </p><p>The new Emergency Care Data Set will be introduced from October 2017, and will improve the recording of the diagnosis of encephalitis in English accident and emergency departments, and allow a greater understanding of the current scope and scale of the problem.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713493/answer",,,,,"69011","2017-03-30T13:35:11.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713493/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713493/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-23","Encephalitis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent steps the Government has taken to improve diagnosis of encephalitis.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","69010"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713494","Department of Health","false","2017-03-30","<p>NHS England and Public Health England are working to raise the profile of familial hypercholesterolaemia (FH) and break down the barriers to genetic testing. Specifically, FH is emphasised in the NHS England Prevention aide memoire to support Sustainability and Transformation Planning, which is available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/stp-aide-memoire-prevention.pdf" target="_blank">www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/stp-aide-memoire-prevention.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>NHS England’s National Clinical Director for heart disease chairs an FH steering group which comprises representatives from relevant stakeholder organisations, including Public Health England. This group, with funding from the British Heart Foundation, has established FH specialist nurses in many areas of England, aimed at increasing FH cascade testing across the country so that more affected families can be identified. The steering group aims to develop a systems approach to the detection and management of FH.</p><p> </p><p>One third of England is now covered by these FH nurses as well as cascade testing, and over the last three years more than 1,000 new people with FH have been identified.</p><p> </p><p>Software to support cascade testing and provide a database for FH is available and will be increasingly used in England as FH services are established.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has also identified FH as a possible condition that it could focus on as part of the work looking into personalised medicine and how the NHS might make better use of increased genetic testing.</p><p> </p><p>Finally, a cholesterol test is included as part of the NHS Health Check that is mandated by the Health and Social Care Act for delivery across all local authorities in England. Revised NHS Best Practice Guidance published in February now includes strengthened guidance for detection of FH as part of the NHS Health Check. Every patient with a cholesterol test result above 7.5mmol/l (as per National Institute for Health and Care Excellence guidance) will be alerted to their general practitioner for consideration of FH in combination with other diagnostic criteria.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713494/answer",,,,,"69040","2017-03-30T14:03:39.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713494/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713494/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-23","Familial Hypercholesterolaemia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that diagnosis and management of familial hypercholesterolaemia is consistent across England.","false","Biography information for Sir Alan Meale","Mansfield","Sir Alan Meale","69039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713495","Department of Health","false","2017-03-30","<p>NHS England and Public Health England are working to raise the profile of familial hypercholesterolaemia (FH) and break down the barriers to genetic testing. Specifically, FH is emphasised in the NHS England Prevention aide memoire to support Sustainability and Transformation Planning, which is available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/stp-aide-memoire-prevention.pdf" target="_blank">www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/stp-aide-memoire-prevention.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>NHS England’s National Clinical Director for heart disease chairs an FH steering group which comprises representatives from relevant stakeholder organisations, including Public Health England. This group, with funding from the British Heart Foundation, has established FH specialist nurses in many areas of England, aimed at increasing FH cascade testing across the country so that more affected families can be identified. The steering group aims to develop a systems approach to the detection and management of FH.</p><p> </p><p>One third of England is now covered by these FH nurses as well as cascade testing, and over the last three years more than 1,000 new people with FH have been identified.</p><p> </p><p>Software to support cascade testing and provide a database for FH is available and will be increasingly used in England as FH services are established.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has also identified FH as a possible condition that it could focus on as part of the work looking into personalised medicine and how the NHS might make better use of increased genetic testing.</p><p> </p><p>Finally, a cholesterol test is included as part of the NHS Health Check that is mandated by the Health and Social Care Act for delivery across all local authorities in England. Revised NHS Best Practice Guidance published in February now includes strengthened guidance for detection of FH as part of the NHS Health Check. Every patient with a cholesterol test result above 7.5mmol/l (as per National Institute for Health and Care Excellence guidance) will be alerted to their general practitioner for consideration of FH in combination with other diagnostic criteria.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713495/answer",,,,,"69039","2017-03-30T14:03:39.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713495/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713495/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-23","Familial Hypercholesterolaemia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to help all clinical commissioning groups to provide adequate access to genetic cascade testing services for familial hypercholesterolemia in their areas.","false","Biography information for Sir Alan Meale","Mansfield","Sir Alan Meale","69040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713496","Department of Health","false","2017-03-30","<p>Annual uptake data is collected at national and local authority level; therefore data is available for Lancashire and England, but not Pendle constituency. The data can be found in the Cover of vaccination evaluated rapidly (COVER) programme reports, available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/vaccine-uptake" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/vaccine-uptake</a></p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713496/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-30T14:05:06.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713496/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713496/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-23","MMR Vaccine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many children have received the MMR vaccination in each year since 2012 in (a) Pendle constituency, (b) Lancashire and (c) England.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","69035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713497","Department of Health","false","2017-03-30","<p>Acute encephalitis is a notifiable disease but given most cases are mild, in practice the majority of cases are not reported. The numbers reported for England and Wales in 2010-15 are available to view here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/572816/NOIDS_Annual_Totals.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/572816/NOIDS_Annual_Totals.xlsx</a></p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713497/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-30T13:40:56.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713497/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713497/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-23","Encephalitis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people have been diagnosed with encephalitis in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","69036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713498","Department of Health","false","2017-03-28","<p>Immunisation to protect against meningococcal disease capsular group B (MenB) has been routinely offered to all infants nationwide since 1 September 2015. This remains the case and there are currently no issues affecting the delivery of this immunisation. Preliminary estimates of MenB vaccine uptake indicate that over 95% of infants received at least one dose of vaccine by 26 weeks of age. A wide range of leaflets and online information have been produced to publicise this important immunisation.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713498/answer",,,,,,"2017-03-28T08:40:14.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713498/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713498/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-23","Meningitis: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department has taken to ensure that the Meningococcal B vaccine is available as appropriate to children in all parts of the country.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","69002"
